  <sect2 role="package">
    <title>Introduction to Xwayland</title>

    <para>
      The <application>Xwayland</application> provides legacy X11 support within Wayland environments.
    </para>

    <para> Please note that this is a pre-release and it is based on xorg server 1.15 code,
    so in order for it to not interfear with your working xorg do NOT change the configure
    line.  It will install into /usr/local and be self-contained.  The release of the 1.16
    version of xorg-server will encorporate xwayland as standard.
    </para>

    &lfs75_checked;

